Debevoise Steers Crescent To Close Record $4.6B Fund



        By Benjamin Horney



					Law360, New York (January 13, 2017,  1:56 PM EST) -- Los Angeles-based credit investment firm Crescent Capital Group LP has closed its largest ever mezzanine debt fund with more than $4.6 billion in tow, the firm said Friday, with help from legal adviser Debevoise & Plimpton LLP.The fund, Crescent Mezzanine Partners VII, blew past its initial fundraising target of $3 billion, according to a statement. Crescent Capital provides debt capital to finance shareholder deals on behalf of private equity firms. The fund has already deployed or committed roughly $900 million from its seventh fund across...
				
